Key Match Events: Michael Leask and Richie Berrington put on 74 runs from 42 balls for the fifth wicket
Richie Berrington smashes it back past David Weise and into hospitality for six big runs
Leask goes! He was down on one knee again but this time he doesn't catch it cleanly and David Wiese is just able to get down to it on the boundary
Post-Match Reflections: Losing captain Gerhard Erasmus reacts to Namibia's loss: 'Unfortunately we let it slip. We scored about par, but then we weren't up to scratch in the field or with the ball.'
Matthew Cross: 'It was an important win. We've given ourselves a chance to go through now so two big games to come.'
Michael Leask: 'A lot of people have come to watch and we repaid that faith. It's a hell of a feeling.'
